Let $p$ be the cost of a pen in cents and $c$ be the cost of a pencil in cents.
We can set up a system of equations:
\begin{align*}
4p + 3c &= 224 \\
2p + 5c &= 154
\end{align*}
We can multiply the second equation by 2 to eliminate $p$:
\begin{align*}
4p + 10c &= 308 \\
4p + 3c &= 224
\end{align*}
Subtracting the second equation from the first, we get $7c = 84$, so $c = \boxed{12}$.
The answer is: 12

